\subsection*{\textcolor{blue}{NUTS with EH}}
\begin{itemize}
\item \textcolor{blue}{Number of steps: {[}201026, 242731{]}}
\item \textcolor{blue}{Step size: 0.01}
\item \textcolor{blue}{Number of tree depth: 8}
\item \textcolor{blue}{Time taken: 13 hours 27 minutes}
\end{itemize}
Thinning is always decreasing the effective sample size. However,
the number of effective samples per sample, $\frac{N_{\text{eff}}}{n}$,
increases until the thinning is large enough that the thinned samples
are uncorrelated.

\begin{table}
